#1 Resected T3, N1 (3 of 13) sigmoid adenocarcinoma
Basic cancer education has been provided to the patient at the request of Dr. Huff Service.  I have had the opportunity to review the operative report, surgical pathology, laboratory values, and notes in Documents Browser.  I have reviewed these findings with the patient and answered questions.  I have discussed this case in detail with Dr. Miller, my collaborating physician, who has guided my plan.
We have discussed the characteristics of the cancer, including the type of malignancy, size, grade, lymph node status, and stage of the cancer.
Mr. Moriarty has a very complicated situation.  We would at this point recommend adjuvant chemotherapy in the form of FOLFOX.  Dr. Miller will visit with Mr. Moriarty prior to dismissal for formal recommendations.  Mr. Moriarty will plan on pursuing adjuvant therapy closer to home in Ansonville North Carolina.  Therefore, I have not made follow-up appointments for him and certainly if the need arises in the future, I am more than happy to facilitate care.
PATIENT EDUCATION:
Ready to learn, no apparent learning barriers were identified; learning preferences include listening.  Explained diagnosis and treatment plan; patient expressed understanding of the content.

